TDD exercise complete. All 10 tests pass across the full Game of Life specification:

**Implementation** (`src/game-of-life.ts`):
- `cellKey` — converts a cell to a string key for Set/Map lookups
- `countNeighbors` — counts live neighbors of a cell (8-connected)
- `nextGeneration` — applies survival (2-3 neighbors) and reproduction (exactly 3 neighbors) rules

**Tests** (`src/game-of-life.spec.ts`):
1. Empty grid → empty
2. Single cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two cells with 1 neighbor each die (underpopulation)
4. Cell with 2 neighbors survives
5. Cell with 3 neighbors survives
6. Cell with >3 neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. Dead cell with <3 neighbors stays dead
9. Block pattern unchanged (still life)
10. Blinker oscillates to alternate form
